sections.Trivia:
- In the "See you next time" sequence at the end of the episode, Amuro tells Akai that "It's been a long time since the ferris wheel". This is a reference to The Darkest Nightmare.
- The names of the suspects are related to musical genres[1]:
- Rokumichi Hado (波土 禄道) comes from "hard rock" (ハードロック hādo rokku);
- Kanae Enjō (円城 佳苗) comes from "enka" (演歌);
- Okuyasu Fuse (布施 憶康, フセ オクヤス in katakana) comes from "folk music" (フォーク, fōku);
- Hirokazu Kajiya (梶谷 宏和, カジヤ ヒロカズ in katakana) comes from "jazz" (ジャズ, jazu).
